quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  89,25,"Then on that Day Allah will chastise as none other can chastise;"
  89,26,"and Allah will bind as none other can bind."
  89,27,"(On the other hand it will be said): “O serene soul!{1}",1:[Peaceful and fully satisfied soul: The man who believed in Allah]
  90,19,"As for those who rejected Our Signs, they are the People of the Left Hand.{1}",1:[For an explanation of the people of the right hand and of the left hand]
  90,20,"Upon them shall be a Fire that will hem them in.{1}",1:[That is, fire will be so covering them from every side that they will find no way of escape from it.]
  92,13,"and to Us belong the Next Life and the present.{1}",1:[This statement has several meanings and all are correct:]
  92,14,"I have now warned you of a Blazing Fire,"
  92,15,"where none shall burn except the most wicked,"
  93,10,"and chide not him who asks,{1}",1:[It has two meanings.]
  93,11,"and proclaim the bounty of your Lord.{1}",1:[The word nimat (bounty) is general]
  94,7,"So, whenever you are free, strive in devotion,"
  94,8,"and turn to your Lord with longing.{1}",1:[So when you have finished (your duties): When you are free from other occupations]
  95,4,"surely We created man in the best mould;{1}",1:[This is the truth for which the oath has been sworn by the lands of the fig and the olive (i.e. Syria and Palestine) and Mt. Sinai and Makkah]
  95,5,"then We reverted him to the lowest of the low,{1}",1:[The commentators in general have given two meanings of this:]
  95,6,"except those who have faith and do righteous deeds. Theirs is a never ending reward.{1}",1:[The commentators who have taken asfala-safilin to imply the state of extreme old age when man loses his sense and reason]
  96,1,"Recite{1} in the name of your Lord{2} Who created,{3}",1:[As we have explained in the Introduction, when the Angel said to the Prophet (peace be upon him): Read, the latter replied: I cannot read! This indicates that the Angel had presented these words of the revelation before him in the written form and had asked him to read them. For if the Angel had meant that he should repeat what he recited, he should not have replied, saying: I cannot read!],2:[Read in the name of your Lord: Say Bismillah and read. This shows that the Prophet (peace be upon him) even before the coming down of this revelation regarded and acknowledged Allah alone as his Lord. That is why there was no need to ask who his Lord was, but it was said: Read in the name of your Lord.],3:[Only the word khalaqa (created) has been used absolutely, and the object of creation has not been mentioned. This automatically gives the meaning: Read in the name of the Lord, Who is the Creator, Who created the whole universe and everything in it.]
  96,2,"created man from a clot of congealed blood.{1}",1:[After making mention generally of the creation of the universe]
  96,3,"Recite: and your Lord is Most Generous,"
